  "text": "Hypoperfusion of the inner ear, thought potentially to cause sudden SNHL in patients under prolonged cardiopulmonary bypass therapy, may also explain the sudden SNHL of BPPV patients [CITATION_1] 17] . Baloh and Honrubia [CITATION_2] found that vascular occlusion of the inner ear caused the release of otoconia from macular utricles. Transient labyrinthine ischemia may trigger patchy loss of inner ear function, associated with sudden SNHL and BPPV/vertigo [17] .",
